    <Parameter>
      <Name>Magnetic field components  in SRV coordinate system</Name>
      <Description>Magnetic field components  in SRV coordinate system. 
Bx, By, Bz: Magnetic field,
Dx, Dy: despin signals corresponding to the continuous magnetic field rotation.

VDH frame (Vertical Dusk Horizontal system)
The V-axis is the outwards local vertical, to the point of observation.The H-axis is parallel to the horizontal local plane, positive to the North.The V-H plane is a geographic meridian plane.  The D-axis is azimuthal, eastwards.
SRV frame
Z aligned with the spin axis
X is in the geographic meridian plane (V,H) of the VDH frame</Description>
      <Caveats>Note that Dx and Dy are truncated from the raw signal before numerisation.
The conversion to Volt units is given by Bx(V) = -(Bx*5.1/255.0 - 2.5)/Gx and Dx(V) = (Dx*5.1/255.0 -2.5)/10.0</Caveats>
